5:
I am Cecilia Cerdic. I live by the sword,
though knighthood was once the 
province of men.
7:
I reached this place after long 
wandering in the dark... You may have 
saved my life.
10:
Until the day comes that I have 
repayed my debt to you, please 
accept my fealty.
17: At last! One who speaks my language!
22:
We welcome your aid, Cecilia. 
We are all wanderers here, searching 
for home.
24:
Thank you.... But before I return, there 
is a task I must see through. I seek a 
woman.
26:
We were together shortly before the 
darkness consumed me. I believe she 
too was sent to a different world.
30: If she was, then we will find her.
32:
Since Light, the World Flipper has 
brought many people to Starview.
33:
We may be able to call her to us. 
I will do my best to locate her.
39:
Now, will you not tell me the customs 
of your land?
50:
But without laws, how can you have 
order?!
59:
Cecilia... In our society, there is none 
of the structure you are accustomed 
to. We live by common sense, not 
laws set into stone and paper.
66: Oh, wait! We DID have a rule!
68:
Any food that goes in the refrigerator 
has to have your name on it!
74:
No customs, no rules besides those
 found in every small household... And
yet folk of all sorts gather here—even 
a sentient mushroom!
76:
What is more, the borders are not 
guarded. People are free to settle here,
or come and go as they please.
78:
And, at all times, there are other 
worlds in the sky... Can I truly live 
here?
81:
That was quite a sigh... Though I 
cannot blame you for it.
87:
I-I'm sorry! I did not mean to be 
ungrateful!
91:
Raise your head. I said I do not blame 
you.
93:
This village is peaceful. A place where 
you can take your ease.
96:
That's true. I see no signs of serious 
conflict or dispute.
98:
There are no laws in Starview... And 
yet, I believe there IS order.
101:
That is because its inhabitants are 
honorable. It's odd, but Alk and Stella 
seem to attract good people.
103:
They are objects of neither devotion 
nor fear. One merely... wishes to see 
them happy.
106:
Yes... I somehow felt that... But people
and circumstances change. 
The future offers no guarantees.
109:
Do you not think some measures 
should be taken to guard against 
unrest?
113: I believe that is why we are here.
117:
Cecilia. Will you not stay and look 
after Alk and Stella?
122: I would be honored to... Champion.
123:
Perhaps I should start by setting up 
a patrol.
126: A fine idea. Allow me to help.
